===Etymology 1===
[[Image:Runic letter ansuz.png|left|30px|Runic letter {{term||áš«|tr=a|ansuz|lang=mul}}, source for Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letters replaced by ''A'']]
From {{etyl|enm|en}} and {{etyl|ang|en}} upper case letter {{term|A|lang=enm}} and split of {{etyl|enm|en}} and {{etyl|ang|en}} upper case letter {{term|Ã†|lang=enm}}.
:* [[Image:Rune-Ac.png|10px|Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letter {{term||ášª|tr=a|Äc|lang=mul}}]] {{etyl|ang|en}} upper case letter {{term|A|lang=enm}} from 7th century replacement by Latin upper case letter {{term|A|lang=la}} of the Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letter {{term|sc=Runr|ášª||tr=a|Äc|lang=mul}}, derived from Runic letter {{term|sc=Runr|áš«||tr=a|Ansuz|lang=mul}}.
:* [[Image:Rune-Ã†sc.png|10px|Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letter {{term||áš«|tr=Ã¦|Ã¦sc|lang=mul}}]] {{etyl|ang|en}} upper case letter {{term|Ã†|lang=enm}} from 7th century replacement by Latin upper case ligature {{term|Ã†|lang=la}} of the Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letter {{term|sc=Runr|áš«||tr=Ã¦|Ã¦sc|lang=mul}}, also derived from Runic letter {{term|sc=Runr|áš«||tr=a|Ansuz|lang=mul}}.

