===Etymology===
Proposed in 1908 as part of the new Latvian spelling by the scientific commission headed by [[w:KÄrlis MÄ«lenbahs|K. MÄ«lenbahs]], which was accepted and began to be taught in schools in 1909. Prior to that, Latvian had been written in German [[Fraktur]], and sporadically in [[Cyrillic]].

