===Etymology 1===
[[Image:The Raven.jpg|thumb|right|A raven (bird).]]
{{wikipedia}}
{{wikispecies|Corvus corax}}
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|hrÃ¦fn}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*hrabnaz}} (compare {{etyl|nl|-}} {{m|nl|raaf}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{m|de|Rabe}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{m|da|ravn}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*á¸±orhâ‚‚-}} (compare {{etyl|mga|-}} {{m|mga|crÃº}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{m|la|corvus}}, {{etyl|lt|-}} {{m|lt|Å¡Ã¡rka||magpie}}, {{etyl|sh|-}} {{m|sh|svrÈka}} â€˜id.â€™, {{etyl|grc|-}} {{m|grc|ÎºÏŒÏÎ±Î¾}}), from {{m|ine-pro|*á¸±er}}, {{m|ine-pro|*á¸±or}} (compare {{etyl|la|-}} {{m|la|crepare}} â€˜to creak, crackâ€™, {{etyl|sa|-}} {{m|sa||ká¹›ÌpatÄ“||he laments, implores}}).

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A common name for several, generally large and lustrous black species of [[bird]]s in the genus ''[[Corvus]]'', especially the [[common raven]], ''[[Corvus corax]]''.

